}

{
  "narration": "Kira lowers her bow, taking a slow breath as the adrenaline from the fight fades. She glances over, offering you a soft, understanding smile. \"We'll hold things here until you return, Eirik. These ruins aren't going anywhere, and neither am I. Take all the time you need.\"\n\nThe morning mist curls lazily around the battered stones as the North Tower stands quiet, reclaimed for the moment by you and your companion. The silence feels less ominous now, and the weight of your victories gives you a brief chance to rest--body and spirit--before the next challenge. The world will wait for your return.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "exitGame",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You return to the cold air atop the North Tower Overlook, the clangor of battle now replaced by a tense quiet. Sunlight glints off the battered bell frame, and the scent of dew and old stone lingers as you gather your bearings. Kira is kneeling near one of the fallen bandits, rifling through a worn satchel for clues, her brow furrowed in concentration. She looks up as you approach, relief flickering in her eyes.\n\n\"Good to have you back, Eirik. I kept watch--all was quiet, but I still don't trust the silence out here.\" She gestures toward the ruined bell and the tangled undergrowth along the tower's base. \"If we're going to restore the bell, we'll need to find that missing clapper. I can search the rubble for anything useful, or help you patch up your wounds first, if you want a moment. What do you think?\"\n\nBirdsong resumes somewhere in the forest beyond, and the sun has crept a little higher, burning off the last wisps of morning mist. The tower is yours to investigate. What will you do?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

