{
  "narration": "The last echo of battle fades as Eirik lowers his mace, the cold morning air thick with the iron scent of blood and the sharp tang of stone. Kira, breathless and battered but on her feet, sheathes her sword and nods her thanks for your healing magic. Around you, two more bandit bodies sprawl amidst the old tower's rubble, grim testament to your defense.\n\nThe North Tower Overlook is eerily quiet once more. The battered bell overhead sways gently, and the first rays of sunlight cut through the mist, illuminating the ground where you now stand victorious. Kira winces as she checks her wounds, but regains her composure quickly. \"That was too close. Thanks, Eirik. I owe you one.\"\n\nYou both take a moment to catch your breath and scan the surroundings for any further threats. The ruins are yours, for now, but the urgency of restoring the bell and searching for clues remains.\n\nWhat do you want to do next?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "HP reduced to 7/11 from crossbow attack; all Level 1 spell slots expended; gained 25 XP (now 50/300)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
