      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You lean heavily against a battered stone, breathing in the sharp scent of moss and distant pine. The echoes of battle fade, and the silence atop the North Tower Overlook grows gentle once more, disturbed only by the soft hum of birdsong and Kira's quiet footsteps as she keeps a cautious watch. She glances over, offering a reassuring nod. \"Rest easy, Eirik. I'll stand guard until you're ready to move again. No one's getting the drop on us this time.\"\n\nThe ruins, sunlit and battered, seem to pause with you--a brief respite before the next challenge. Take all the time you need; your place in the story will await your return.",
