{
  "narration": "You return to the exposed heights of the North Tower Overlook, the ruined bell frame creaking softly overhead as sunlight glimmers off mossy stone and drying blood. Kira stands nearby, her bow resting at her side, eyes sharp on the horizon. She offers you a relieved smile as you rejoin her.\n\n\"Welcome back, Eirik. Quiet as a graveyard while you were gone,\" she says with a chuckle, though her voice is edged with relief. \"No more bandits, at least for now. Shall we get back to it? We still need to search for that missing bell clapper and see if these bandits left behind anything useful. Or, if you need to catch your breath, just say the word.\"\n\nThe soft spring wind stirs the mist below, carrying the scent of pine and distant river water. The tower is yours once more--the next step is yours to choose.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira dusts her hands off and glances toward the battered corpses among the tumbled stone. \"Just two, Eirik. The only bandits stationed here at the North Tower Overlook were these two--the ones we just fought. Their job was to keep anyone from repairing the bell or poking around. We took them both down, and as far as I can tell, that's all that were assigned here.\"\n\nShe nudges one of the bandits with her boot and surveys the perimeter. \"Doesn't look like they were expecting reinforcements or another patrol anytime soon, either. For now, the tower is ours. Let's see if they left us any clues, or if we can find that missing bell clapper.\"\n\nThe quiet that follows seems deeper, as if the forest itself is waiting for your next move.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

