{
  "narration": "Kira kneels beside the fallen bandits, her expression sharp with focus as she begins to search their battered forms and scattered gear. She glances up at you, gesturing for you to check the other. \"Let's see if these two were carrying anything useful--orders, coins, clues about the sabotage, or even the bell clapper. Never know what desperate men hold onto.\"\n\nYou crouch down, the cold stone pressing through your gloves as you begin your search. The bandits' pockets are full of dirt and fragments of broken trail rations. Kira finds a crumpled scrap of parchment tucked into a leather vest, stained with sweat and hastily scrawled notes: coded watch schedules and a rough map of ranger patrol routes. She also unearths a small pouch jingling with silver coins, likely stolen from a trader or ranger. A coil of sturdy climbing rope and a half-empty waterskin round out the haul. As you move to the second bandit, your hand brushes against something solid hidden in the undergrowth--a gleam of polished silver nearly swallowed by moss and leaves. It's the missing bell clapper, crudely wrapped in oiled cloth to smother any sound.\n\nKira's eyes widen in triumph as you hold up the prize. \"That's it! The bell clapper! Luck's finally on our side, Eirik.\"\n\nTogether, you've uncovered both evidence of insider sabotage and the means to repair the North Tower's bell. The outpost's lifeline is within reach again.",
