{
  "narration": "Kira flashes a grateful smile, clearly relieved to have your steady presence watching her back. She moves with careful purpose toward the battered bell frame, cradling the recovered silver clapper in one hand while examining the damaged fittings with the other. The air is crisp with the scent of moss and cold iron, punctuated by the occasional settling groan of ancient stone.\n\nYou stand sentry, eyes flicking from the forest edge to the ruined trail as Kira climbs up the rickety platform. She unspools the climbing rope, knots it deftly, and secures herself before working. Her hands are steady, and she hums quietly--a habit when focused on a delicate task.\n\nAtop the platform, Kira first cleans old grease and sand from the bell's socket, then carefully seats the clapper, using a small hammer to tap the fittings snug. The faint sound echoes down into the clearing, and a feeling of hope stirs in your chest.\n\nAfter several tense minutes, she gives a triumphant thumbs-up. \"All set, Eirik! Ready to ring her as soon as we want. I'd say this is a win for the Rangers.\"\n\nYour vigilant watch ensures that no one--bandit or beast--disturbs the repairs. The North Tower's bell is restored, and for the first time in days, the outpost's warning system stands ready.\n\nWhat would you like to do next? Ring the bell to signal the command post, search the area further, or head to your next destination?",
  "actions": [
