{
  "narration": "Kira grins wide, exhilaration lighting her features as she gives you a thumbs-up from the platform. \"Ready when you are!\" she calls down. You nod, stepping back to give her space as she takes the thick, newly-secured rope in hand.\n\nWith a deep breath, Kira throws her weight into the first pull. The mighty bell peals out over the treetops, a triumphant note of hope and warning that echoes across the wilds and down to the distant outpost. The sound reverberates through stone and bone alike, scattering a flock of startled crows and sending a ripple of excitement through the misty air.\n\nFor the first time in days, the silver bell's call rings clear, announcing to friend and foe alike that the Rangers' vigilance endures. Kira laughs, her voice lifted by relief. \"That ought to wake the command post! We've done it, Eirik! The network's alive again. I only wish the others could see this.\"\n\nThe moment hangs golden with pride and accomplishment. Soon, the outpost will hear the news and know help is at hand. You and Kira stand together, guardians of the North Tower once more, with the horizon stretching wide before you.\n\nWhat do you wish to do next--search for further clues, head for another bell tower, or report your success to Commander Elen?",
  "actions": [
